  .section-content

    .work-experince
      .work-duration
        p Now
        p Jul/2017
      .work-title
        a(target="_blank" href="http://www.stone.com.br/")
          p.company Stone Pagamentos
        p.title Developer
      .work-description
        p At Stone I work as a developer for
          i  Point-of-Sale
          |  machines (embedded). I work on building applications for the card machine, using a
          span(title="Single Page Application")  SPA
          |  framework developed by the company itself (based on
          i  VueJS
          |  ). Currently I dedicate myself to creation and improvements of the POS apps, as well as to training new partners.
        p I am also part of a innersource project, this time as a
          b  designer
          |  that intend to establish proper deploy and monitoring flows. Due to it's high complexity I'm appling
          a(href="https://alistapart.com/article/object-oriented-ux")  OOUX
          | , while also mentoring other designers on the methodology.
        ul.tools
          li(title="Javascript") JS
          li Node
          li(title="ECMAScript 6") ES6
          li(title="Framework developed by company") Web Components
          li HTML
          li CSS (Sass)
          li Webpack
          li Git
          li Jekyll
          li Embedded
          li OOUX

    .work-experince
      .work-duration
        p Jun/2017
        p Nov/2016
      .work-title
        a(target="_blank" href="http://www.comidadagente.org/")
          p.company Comida da Gente
        p.title Business Analyst & Operations Manager
      .work-description
        p As Operations Manager for
          a(target="_blank" href="http://www.comidadagente.org/")  Comida da Gente
          |, I’ve managed and run several collaborative purchases from small local producers. I took care of organizing the logistics for the purchases, which included gathering people, making sure the purchase everything went smoothly for consumers and producers, overseeing the deliveries and keep an eye on the pick-ups. Alongside with the CEO, we’ve co-managed the operations and communication team. From customer service to negotiating with the producers, all tasks had to be done. Every now and then some crisis handling had to be done due to unexpected situations. I could experiment with different service design ideas to improve the consumer's experience. The closeness to the users made it easy to get feedback and come up with new ideas and solutions. As Business Analyst I would evaluate the producer's performance and experiment with new strategies. I'd look for new producers as well as welcome and support new producers when joining the community. I' keep an eye on their sales performance and analyze it. Whenever need, we'd come up with new strategies for each producer individually on how to improve. All the data was inputed on Spreadsheets and I came to develop scripts to aid some tasks.
        ul.tools
          li Spreadsheet
          li Design Thinking
          li Crisis Handling
          li Service Design
          li Adobe Illustrator
          li Adobe Photoshop
          li Google App Scripts
          li(title="Javascript") JS

    .work-experince
      .work-duration
        p Nov/2016
        p Jun/2015
      .work-title
        a(target="_blank" href="http://www.comidadagente.org/")
          p.company Comida da Gente
        p.title Product Designer
      .work-description
        p My role in the
          a(target="_blank" href="http://www.comidadagente.org/")  Comida da Gente
          |  platform began as a part of my graduation project in Design, which was the design of an online platform that would comprehend the necessities of the initiative. The project itself was highly praised and got the maximum grade. From February to November I worked alone on all the tasks regarding the structuring of the platform. I got to do some borad research (collaborative economy, organic produces), user research (interviewing producers, consumers, working alongside producers), interviews with stakeholders, user journey, information architecture (using object-oriented paradigm), strategy, navigation, sketches, wireframes, high-fidelity prototyping (HTML/JS/SASS), heuristics, usability tests (nine tests, within an age and familiarity with technology range).
        ul.tools
          li Adobe Illustrator
          li Adobe Photoshop
          li HTML (Pug)
          li CSS (Sass)
          li JS (JQuery)
          li Usability Test
          li Information Architecture
          li User Research
        .extra-material
          a.behance.article(target="_blank" href="https://www.behance.net/gallery/48843815/Comida-da-Gente-Producers")
            img.small(src="assets/behance_cdg_producers_small.png")
            img(src="assets/behance_cdg_producers.png")
          a.behance.article(target="_blank" href="https://www.behance.net/gallery/49478311/Comida-da-Gente-Catalogue")
            img.small(src="assets/behance_cdg_catalogue_small.png")
            img(src="assets/behance_cdg_catalogue.png")

